evals.prompt:
I have a handler that calls context.Fail() when a scope claim is missing. Users are being denied even though they have another handler that should grant access. What's wrong and how do I fix it?

```csharp
public class ScopeHandler : AuthorizationHandler<ApiAccessRequirement>
{
    protected override Task HandleRequirementAsync(
        AuthorizationHandlerContext context, ApiAccessRequirement requirement)
    {
        if (!context.User.HasClaim("scope", "api.read"))
            context.Fail();
        else
            context.Succeed(requirement);
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }
}
```
